    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-30T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-30T06:00:00-05:00" n="731"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d731">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/5334: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Leopoldville</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mallon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Leopoldville</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-30T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 30, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 30—10:40
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my telegram of August 28 De Larminat appointed High Commissioner of
                    France Libre for French Equatorial Africa and Cameroon. <hi rend="italic">Coup
                        d’état</hi> effected without bloodshed. Husson roughly handled but unhurt,
                    expects to leave Leopoldville for Dakar as soon as possible. Should I call
                    officially on De Larminat?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mallon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
